data.title: BenQ XR3501 Curved Monitor Interview
data.tags: 144Hz Refresh Rate,AMVA Curved,Black eQualizer,Zero flicker,HDMI1.4x2,Headphone jack,Mic jack,BenQ,XR3501,21:9,Ultra Wide Curve,LED,Backlight,Gaming Professional Monitor,game mode,Newegg,Newegg.com,Newegg TV,NeweggTV,review,technology,video,electronics,de
data.description:
Here's a curved monitor, made by BenQ, Model: XR3501. Check out the video for more info!

Discover a truly immersive viewing experience while working and playing with the BenQ XR3501 35" curved monitor. Designed and optimized for gaming especially the racing gaming, the XR3501 boasts a curvature of 2000R - the most of any monitor released yet, and an ultra-wide 21:9 aspect ratio. These together deliver immersive and panoramic viewing that covers your natural field of vision down to the periphery. It features 2560 x 1080 resolution, plus 144Hz refresh rate that render smooth and crisp images even in the fastest action scene.

BenQ XR3501 Curved Monitor Interview

data.title: ASUS  Zenbook  UX305FA-ASM1 13.3" Ultrabook Interview
data.description: ASUS ZenBook is lighter, slimmer and faster than other notebooks in its class to give you the unmatched power and all-day portability you need to conquer your day. And when other glossy notebooks show more glare than what’s actually on the screen, ASUS ZenBook always shines through even the sunniest days thanks to the 13-inch matte anti-glare wide-angle IPS display. Featuring the new Intel Core M processor, do more with faster speeds and enhanced efficiency that automatically adjusts performance to what you’re doing. Add to that the incredible responsiveness of the Solid State Drive (SSD), everything from startup to loading demanding programs happens in a flash. And like the silent power of an electric sports car, the fanless processor and SSD give you all the power you want--without any of the noise.
